nd rugs.\n\r','',0,0,1,100,100,0),(980,5224,'Under the watchtower','You stand under one of the city watchtowers built to protect\n\rthe city from invaders. Obviously, it failed.\n\r','',0,0,1,100,100,0),(981,5225,'The jewelery stand','A table has been tipped over, spilling fine jewelery and gems\n\racross the market place. Most of these trinkets are battered and\n\rtarnished and few would have any value anymore.\n\r','',0,0,1,100,100,0),(982,5226,'A ruined clay dwelling','This was once a very plain house with nothing more than a few chairs\n\rand a bed. A cold fireplace suggests that the city has been abandoned\n\rfor quite a while. Almost nothing remains of this humble abode.\n\r','',8,0,1,100,100,0),(983,5227,'A collapsed stone dwelling','This small house has completely collapsed upon itself leaving piles\n\rof debris here and there. A few rafters still stand with thatched straw\n\rhanging down and a hot wind gusts through the hollow dwelling.\n\r','',0,0,1,100,100,0),(984,5228,'A back alley','A narrow alley leads east to one of the city watchtowers and west to\n\ra small side street.\n\r','',0,0,1,100,100,0),(985,5229,'An abandoned shop','From the outside this place looks like an ordinary pile of rubble,\n\rbut inside these cramped quarters you discover what used to be a shop\n\rfilled with armor, weapons, and various other goods. A small sign flutters\n\rin the wind.\n\r','',8,0,1,100,100,0),(986,5230,'The Tavern of the Sun','A glorious place in it\'s prime, this tavern now lies in ruin; tables\n\rand chairs are broken scattered, bottles and glasses shattered, and\n\ra small performance stage crushed. Musical instruments and personal\n\rbelongings lie under the rubble, but the people they once belonged to are\n\rnot with them. Looking up you see that the entire second floor and roof\n\rhas fallen in, leaving a gaping hole above.\n\r','',0,0,1,100,100,0),(987,5231,'South wing of the city hall','You stand in a large room attached to this end of the hallway which\n